       </table></item>
       <item xmlns="http://cnx.rice.edu/cnxml">The dominance of connectives explains the order in which compound logical statements containing multiple connectives should be interpreted.</item>
    <item xmlns="http://cnx.rice.edu/cnxml">The dominance of connectives should be applied in the following order
     <list id="list-00013">
       <item>Parentheses</item>
       <item>Negations</item>
